00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:35,360
So you let him hold you?

282
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:36,800
So you let that guy hold you?

283
00:12:36,800 --> 00:12:37,510
NO!

284
00:12:37,510 --> 00:12:40,160
I let him do it, because I loved him.

285
00:12:41,120 --> 00:12:43,000
You truly loved him?

286
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:44,120
Obviously!

287
00:12:44,120 --> 00:12:47,070
He accepted what I truly was.

288
00:12:47,070 --> 00:12:47,840
Really?

289
00:12:47,840 --> 00:12:49,500
He was tender.

290
00:13:02,020 --> 00:13:02,950
NO!

291
00:13:02,950 --> 00:13:05,610
Don't show this to Shinji-kun!

292
00:13:06,940 --> 00:13:09,460
You don't have to be ashamed of that moment.

293
00:13:09,460 --> 00:13:11,120
I am ashamed of it.

294
00:13:11,120 --> 00:13:12,950
Why feel shame?

295
00:13:12,950 --> 00:13:15,090
You can show it to the guy you love.

296
00:13:15,090 --> 00:13:18,160
Moreover, you wish to show this.

297
00:13:18,690 --> 00:13:20,470
NO! Stop!

298
00:13:22,010 --> 00:13:24,940
You must be glad to show this to Shinji.

299
00:13:24,940 --> 00:13:26,680
NO!

300
00:13:26,680 --> 00:13:28,400
NO! NO WAY!

301
00:13:28,400 --> 00:13:29,980
I wonder.

302
00:13:29,980 --> 00:13:32,620
It's to your father that you wan to show this.

303
00:13:32,620 --> 00:13:33,890
NO!

304
00:13:33,890 --> 00:13:37,530
You tried to find peace in Kaji-kun's arms.

305
00:13:37,530 --> 00:13:38,620
NO!

306
00:13:38,620 --> 00:13:41,800
You tried to find a peace in Kaji-kun's kindness.

307
00:13:41,800 --> 00:13:42,820
NO!

308
00:13:42,820 --> 00:13:46,670
You tried to find your father in Kaji-kun's arms.

309
00:13:46,670 --> 00:13:47,970
NO!

310
00:13:50,240 --> 00:13:51,340
YES.

311
00:13:51,340 --> 00:13:55,950
I found the father within Kaji-kun back then.

312
00:13:56,680 --> 00:13:58,260
So I fled from him.

313
00:13:58,260 --> 00:13:59,390
I feared.

314
00:14:00,870 --> 00:14:02,790
He was just like my father.

315
00:14:05,590 --> 00:14:07,760
But, it was because I was happy,

316
00:14:07,760 --> 00:14:10,160
It was a joy.

317
00:14:10,160 --> 00:14:12,900
It was truly an enjoyable joy!

318
00:14:13,480 --> 00:14:14,910
So I did hate.

319
00:14:14,910 --> 00:14:16,850
So I did separate.

320
00:14:18,800 --> 00:14:23,770
No reason to begin love, but a reason to end the love.

321
00:14:24,730 --> 00:14:27,250
You are so kind..

322
00:14:27,250 --> 00:14:33,750
You are so kind.. So I beg you, disgrace me.

323
00:14:36,040 --> 00:14:40,140
Don't hurt yourself only because you hate yourself now.

324
00:14:40,140 --> 00:14:45,050
Punishing yourself is only a trick to make you feel better for a little while.

325
00:14:45,900 --> 00:14:47,280
Don't do that.

326
00:14:47,870 --> 00:14:51,710
Andnow you're going to say, "you must take care of yourself"?

327
00:14:51,710 --> 00:14:54,410
Guys always do so.

328
00:14:54,410 --> 00:14:59,820
And Guys work, and Guys go into their world, leaving me behind.

329
00:15:00,860 --> 00:15:03,280
Just like my father.

330
00:15:03,280 --> 00:15:06,480
Always trying to escape from the hardships in reality.

331
00:15:06,480 --> 00:15:09,000
Hardship in reality?

332
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:10,310
It's me?

333
00:15:10,310 --> 00:15:12,700
It's me. Yes. It's me.

334
00:15:12,700 --> 00:15:14,600
It's inevitable.

335
00:15:15,700 --> 00:15:17,400
Stop, Misato-san.

336
00:15:18,380 --> 00:15:20,350
I despise myself.

337
00:15:20,350 --> 00:15:21,890
I hate myself!

338
00:15:21,890 --> 00:15:22,850
You're vulgar and impure.

339
00:15:22,850 --> 00:15:23,990
Pathetic!

340
00:15:23,990 --> 00:15:27,300
Disgusting! You're a dirty whore!

341
00:15:27,300 --> 00:15:30,470
Is that the adults' intercourse?
I really hate that!

342
00:15:30,470 --> 00:15:34,340
Congratulations with you promotion. Major Katsuragi.

343
00:15:34,340 --> 00:15:36,230
The Me who is recognized is the Me who is performing

344
00:15:36,230 --> 00:15:38,680
a role in order to be appreciated.

345
00:15:38,680 --> 00:15:40,650
It's not the true Me.

346
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:44,000
The true Me is always crying.

347
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:46,790
Yes. I am happy!

348
00:15:46,790 --> 00:15:47,520
Am I happy?

349
00:15:47,520 --> 00:15:49,630
I am happy.

350
00:15:49,630 --> 00:15:50,740
Am I happy?

351
00:15:50,740 --> 00:15:52,880
I am happy....?

352
00:15:52,880 --> 00:15:53,880
Am I happy?

353
00:15:53,880 --> 00:15:54,930
NO!

354
00:15:54,930 --> 00:15:56,590
This is not happiness!

355
00:15:56,590 --> 00:15:57,620
What's happiness?

356
00:15:57,620 --> 00:16:00,030
This is not the true Me!

357
00:16:00,030 --> 00:16:02,300
I am only trying to think so.

358
00:16:02,860 --> 00:16:05,940
Otherwise, we cannot live?

359
00:16:06,410 --> 00:16:08,480
We are unstable unless we are together.

360
00:16:08,480 --> 00:16:09,560
Unstable.

361
00:16:09,560 --> 00:16:11,790
Unless someone is in the same bed.

362
00:16:11,790 --> 00:16:13,720
You are afraid to sleep alone?

363
00:16:13,720 --> 00:16:16,830
You are tired of sleeping alone?

364
00:16:16,830 --> 00:16:19,650
Or does sleeping alone remind you of how empty your life is?

365
00:16:19,650 --> 00:16:22,030
Then, Anybody will do.

366
00:16:22,030 --> 00:16:23,660
NO!

367
00:16:23,660 --> 00:16:26,980
YES, you wish to get some simple joy.

368
00:16:26,980 --> 00:16:30,420
You are trying to cure your mind with temporary escape.

369
00:16:30,420 --> 00:16:33,020
You are making use of GUYS.

370
00:16:33,520 --> 00:16:35,730
NO NO NO WAY!

371
00:16:37,730 --> 00:16:39,260
What does she really wish?

372
00:16:41,100 --> 00:16:42,860
Where am I?

373
00:16:43,890 --> 00:16:46,330
It's my mind within Asuka's.

374
00:16:46,810 --> 00:16:50,940
Then, it's my mind within Shinji.

375
00:16:51,430 --> 00:16:52,920
In the case of Soryuu Asuka Langley.

376
00:16:53,540 --> 00:16:55,300
What do you hope?

377
00:16:56,300 --> 00:16:58,200
I can live alone.

378
00:16:58,200 --> 00:17:00,060
I don't need either daddy or mom.

379
00:17:00,060 --> 00:17:01,370
I live alone.

380
00:17:01,370 --> 00:17:03,040
I won't cry anymore.

381
00:17:05,420 --> 00:17:07,310
Yet, I am crying.

382
00:17:07,310 --> 00:17:08,800
Why am I crying?

383
00:17:11,210 --> 00:17:13,380
It's difficult for me to deal with that child.

384
00:17:14,380 --> 00:17:17,970
That's not like you, a doctor.

385
00:17:17,970 --> 00:17:19,710
A Doctor is a human being,

386
00:17:19,710 --> 00:17:21,560
as I said before.

387
00:17:21,560 --> 00:17:25,450
Still, you're a traind professional, how can you...

388
00:17:25,450 --> 00:17:29,080
She acts too much like an adult, and rejects me completely.

389
00:17:29,080 --> 00:17:32,120
Sometimes she scares me.

390
00:17:32,120 --> 00:17:34,820
Haven't you had that feeling with her?

391
00:17:34,820 --> 00:17:36,210
Well,

392
00:17:36,210 --> 00:17:39,860
Anyhow, you are Asuka's mother, after all.

393
00:17:39,860 --> 00:17:43,620
I became your wife before that.

394
00:17:43,620 --> 00:17:45,200
Aren't you both?

395
00:17:45,200 --> 00:17:47,950
From a social persective, yes.

396
00:17:47,950 --> 00:17:51,140
However, I can quit being her mother at anytime.

397
00:17:51,140 --> 00:17:55,150
...but you cannot quit being her father.

398
00:17:55,150 --> 00:17:56,450
Well, you could say that.

399
00:17:56,450 --> 00:17:57,390
NO! STOP!

400
00:17:57,390 --> 00:17:59,490
Don't quit being my mother!

401
00:17:59,490 --> 00:18:02,260
I'll be a good child!

402
00:18:02,260 --> 00:18:04,470
So, don't quit being my mother.

403
00:18:04,470 --> 00:18:06,400
So, look at me!

404
00:18:06,400 --> 00:18:09,600
Stop MOM, don't kill me!

405
00:18:10,500 --> 00:18:13,000
Your daddy hates your mommy.

406
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:15,130
Your daddy deserted me.

407
00:18:15,130 --> 00:18:18,570
No, he never loved me to begin with.

408
00:18:18,570 --> 00:18:21,600
He didn't need me at all.

409
00:18:21,600 --> 00:18:24,520
So, let's die together with mom.

410
00:18:24,520 --> 00:18:27,130
Daddy does not need us.

411
00:18:27,130 --> 00:18:28,520
Am I a waste?

412
00:18:28,520 --> 00:18:29,800
Am I useless?

413
00:18:30,720 --> 00:18:32,820
Let's die together.

414
00:18:32,820 --> 00:18:33,740
NO!

415
00:18:33,740 --> 00:18:36,060
I'm not your doll.

416
00:18:36,060 --> 00:18:38,980
I can think by myself, I can live by myself.

417
00:18:41,180 --> 00:18:44,510
Then, my mommy was hanging from the cealing.

418
00:18:45,200 --> 00:18:47,930
She looked so happy.

419
00:18:48,860 --> 00:18:52,610
But I hated her face back then.

420
00:18:53,290 --> 00:18:54,760
I don't wanna die.

421
00:18:54,760 --> 00:18:57,290
I don't wanna let myself disappear.

422
00:18:57,290 --> 00:18:58,960
I don't like boys.

423
00:18:58,960 --> 00:19:01,180
I don't like daddy, mom.

424
00:19:01,180 --> 00:19:03,060
I don't like anybody!

425
00:19:03,060 --> 00:19:05,700
Nobody protects me.

426
00:19:05,700 --> 00:19:07,780
Nobody is by me.

427
00:19:07,780 --> 00:19:09,330
What does she wish?

428
00:19:10,290 --> 00:19:11,920
So, I do live alone.

429
00:19:12,600 --> 00:19:13,930
But I don't want that.

430
00:19:13,930 --> 00:19:15,660
It's painful.

431
00:19:15,660 --> 00:19:16,950
I don't wanna be alone.

432
00:19:16,950 --> 00:19:19,080
I don't wanna be alone.

433
00:19:19,080 --> 00:19:21,640
I don't wanna be alone!

434
00:19:24,280 --> 00:19:25,880
Don't leave me.

435
00:19:25,880 --> 00:19:27,400
Don't desert me.

436
00:19:27,400 --> 00:19:29,180
Don't kill me.

437
00:19:31,760 --> 00:19:33,130
What's this?

438
00:19:35,170 --> 00:19:37,360
This is the Instrumentality of Man project that

439
00:19:37,360 --> 00:19:39,980
your father has been carrying out.

440
00:19:39,980 --> 00:19:40,520
This is it?

441
00:19:40,520 --> 00:19:42,170
This is part of it, I think.

442
00:19:42,170 --> 00:19:45,230
The truth is yet unknown to us.

443
00:19:45,230 --> 00:19:50,130
The things you perceive constitute the truth.

444
00:19:50,130 --> 00:19:52,280
Things within you.

445
00:19:52,280 --> 00:19:56,860
And the things recorded in your memory will be your truth.

446
00:19:56,860 --> 00:20:00,100
There is a truth that changes through time.

447
00:20:00,100 --> 00:20:01,340
This is the truth.

448
00:20:01,340 --> 00:20:04,140
The result of everything, is this?

449
00:20:04,140 --> 00:20:07,170
Out of many truths, one is this.

450
00:20:07,170 --> 00:20:10,010
That's the result you wished.

451
00:20:10,010 --> 00:20:11,670
I wished?

452
00:20:11,670 --> 00:20:12,750
Yes.

453
00:20:12,750 --> 00:20:16,240
The destruction, the world, where nobody would be saved.

454
00:20:16,240 --> 00:20:19,280
NO. It's that nobody saved me.

455
00:20:19,280 --> 00:20:22,500
Nobody can save you.

456
00:20:22,500 --> 00:20:25,200
This is what you wished for.

457
00:20:25,200 --> 00:20:28,910
The destruction, the death, the return to nothingness.

458
00:20:28,910 --> 00:20:30,630
All of these, you did wish.

459
00:20:30,630 --> 00:20:32,550
This is the reality.

460
00:20:32,550 --> 00:20:34,520
What's the reality?

461
00:20:34,520 --> 00:20:36,460
Your world.

462
00:20:36,460 --> 00:20:41,190
With time, with space, with other people, the world of your own.

463
00:20:41,190 --> 00:20:44,100
The world where how to accept things and how to perceive things

464
00:20:44,100 --> 00:20:46,030
are absolutely up to you.

465
00:20:46,030 --> 00:20:49,500
It's the world where you just wait for others to give you something.

466
00:20:49,700 --> 00:20:50,860
That is reality.

467
00:20:51,410 --> 00:20:53,880
This is your world no matter what.

468
00:20:53,880 --> 00:20:57,070
It's the the world where everything is already set isn't it?

469
00:20:57,070 --> 00:20:59,890
No, it's the world that you are setting.

470
00:21:00,390 --> 00:21:04,230
The world where your mind decides what will be.

471
00:21:04,230 --> 00:21:05,280
That's the reality.

472
00:21:05,280 --> 00:21:07,520
Whether it's the will to live.

473
00:21:07,520 --> 00:21:11,360
or the wish to die, that is up to you.

474
00:21:11,360 --> 00:21:14,330
Are you saying that this darkness, this insane world...

475
00:21:14,330 --> 00:21:16,640
are what I wished?

476
00:21:16,640 --> 00:21:17,650
Yes.

477
00:21:17,650 --> 00:21:20,220
A closed world where nobody but you is comfortable.

478
00:21:20,220 --> 00:21:21,700
That is the very world you wished for.

479
00:21:21,700 --> 00:21:24,720
To protect your weak mind.

480
00:21:24,720 --> 00:21:27,350
To protect your joy.

481
00:21:27,350 --> 00:21:29,780
This is the result.

482
00:21:29,780 --> 00:21:33,130
In a closed space with nobody but you in it,

483
00:21:33,130 --> 00:21:36,430
others cannot live.

484
00:21:36,430 --> 00:21:39,590
But you wished the world to close on yourself.

485
00:21:39,590 --> 00:21:43,260
Excluding what you hate, you wished a world of solitude.

486
00:21:44,620 --> 00:21:49,560
That's the world you created, a private haven in the recesses of your mind.

487
00:21:50,820 --> 00:21:54,000
This is one of the possible conclusions.

488
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:57,800
A fate which you chose.

489
00:21:59,390 --> 00:22:00,670
Instrumentality continues...

